# ESLint SOP

- Match project config (flat `eslint.config.*` or legacy `.eslintrc`); do not fork rules without reason.
- Run lint before marking UI/API tasks done (`npm run lint` or project script).
- Fix auto-fixable issues; suppressions require comment + ticket/issue ref.
- No unused vars/imports in new code; align import order with repo plugin.
- Prefer consistent quote/semi rules already in config — no style wars in mixed PRs.
- Type-aware rules: use `@typescript-eslint` when TS project already does.
- CI must mirror local lint command when scaffold provides `.github/workflows`.
